\section{Application Architecture}

The web application, \textbf{IMDb Explorer}, is a server-side rendered Node.js
application using the Express.js framework. All database interactions are handled
on the server; the client receives only fully rendered HTML pages.

\begin{table}[H]
\centering
\caption{Technology Stack}
\begin{tabular}{l l l}
  \toprule
  \textbf{Layer} & \textbf{Technology} & \textbf{Purpose} \\
  \midrule
  Database      & MySQL 8 (InnoDB)     & Persistent data storage \\
  DB Client     & mysql2 (NPM)         & Async query execution, connection pool \\
  Runtime       & Node.js              & Server-side JavaScript \\
  Framework     & Express.js           & HTTP routing and middleware \\
  Templating    & EJS                  & Server-side HTML rendering \\
  Styling       & Vanilla CSS          & Custom ``Cinematic Scholar'' design system \\
  Charts        & Chart.js v4 (CDN)    & Client-side data visualisation \\
  Config        & dotenv (NPM)         & Credentials via \texttt{.env} file \\
  \bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\label{tab:stack}
\end{table}

